# Implement SparseBoundedGrid

The goal is to add a new type of grid (SparseBoundedGrid) to the GridWorld project. This implementation will use a `HashMap` for efficiency in sparse grids and will be located in a separate project directory.

## Proposed Changes

### [SparseGrid Project]

#### [NEW] [SparseBoundedGrid.java](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/GridWorld/src/GridWorldCode/projects/sparseGrid/SparseBoundedGrid.java)
Implement a bounded grid that uses a `Map` to store occupants, optimized for grids with few occupants. No comments will be included.

#### [NEW] [SparseGridRunner.java](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/GridWorld/src/GridWorldCode/projects/sparseGrid/SparseGridRunner.java)
A runner class to demonstrate and test the `SparseBoundedGrid`.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Compile the new files using `javac`.
2. Run `SparseGridRunner` to ensure the grid behaves correctly (adding/removing actors, valid locations).
3. Observe the GridWorld GUI to confirm actors are placed and moved correctly in the sparse grid.
